No. Oh no. No, you couldn't - them days - even when I went there to work you used to have make your tea in a - can. Boil your water in a can and then pitch your - tea, sugar a
nd milk - condensed milk - made up what they used to call a batch, that used to be a part of your - lunch. In a - in a paper bag. A batch of tea, sugar and milk, all mixed together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You'd bring that from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And then you'd tip this - and 
