\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well - the - the regular clothing then was just the - their ordinary - odd trouser
s and a jacket with a scarf round their neck. Always had a scarf round their neck, never had a collar and tie on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But they always wore a scarf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Mufflers they called them. And cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Wel
l, a little I suppose, I used to hear him crack on about - these different Conservatives and the Liberals, but of course he was rank Labour. You had to be Labour - because when I was a boy - they used to go round in groups - and - when the election was - 
p
ending, I can remember once was - Will Thorne and Jack Jones. And Will Thorne - was Conservative. Now as I've got older. And when this gang of boys come along we just had to - try and guess - and they'd come up to you with sticks you see and say, who do y
ou vote for? And we'd have to guess and - sort of work it out and if it was - if we said the wrong thing, as you might say Will Thorne you was let go but if you said Jack Jones and - the Labour candidate you'd get a bashing. Pick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3547903\charrsid2953716 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 staff lying about. That was a common thing that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you take that just as an example or would they always be inclined to bash you up if you said a Labour person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would most of these gangs be supporting the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 We'd be out - proba
bly we'd be out - the - little bit classy area you see going towards Wanstead Flats. You see, 'cos that was a big playing place, fiel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3547903\charrsid2953716 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 s and it was a little bit classy there. And when we - we'd meet this gang coming along - and we - we'd have to between ourselves with commonsense say, Will Thorne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Because they were from more Conservative homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They were more Conservative round that area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there gangs from around your part who'd be supporting Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Labour, oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would this be quite young children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh boys, yes, boys between - nine, ten or twelve years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you wear colours, the party colours at all?
