articular night - I got caught. And the watchman caught me, and took me away and locked me up in a - in a - a square that hadn't got any roof to it. But - before that we had to climb over two fences - and this old fellow he fell - fell backwards on the fe
nce, and I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3547903\charrsid2953716 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305937\charrsid2953716 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3547903\charrsid2953716 ppy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
 enough to - help him to get straight, instead of running away, I helped him to get up then he locked me up into this - compound - to catch the other boys, but when he'd gone I whipped over the top so I was gone when he came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were the police out and about a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes, very - yes, very often. And if they caught you they would - they wouldn't - scare you with the name and address business. Well they didn't with us, they used to - whack you with their gloves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they ever go to take a boy back home and talk to his parents or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Not that I know of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your parents ever go out to sit in a pub and drink in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, very very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They didn't drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not in a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They'd get stuff in from the off licence if they wanted it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes. Yes, it used to be a - regular thing that did really. With lots of families. The off licence used to do near as much trade as what a pub did didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was it cheaper that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, more convenience of having it indoors, but of course used to take a jug round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did the children take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, children - if children went - they used to have to get it in a bottle. And - and they'd seal it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So the children couldn't drink it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Couldn't drink it. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So your mother or father went themselves did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 To get it in a jug, yes, unless you was fourteen. Then you were allowed - to go and get it, but - when they've had does, we've - I've g
one as a boy - and got - gallons of beer in a gallon - jar, but you could get that but it still had to be sealed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It was beer they would drink was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Not anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not really. 'Cos whisky then - was three and six a bottle. I do know that. A pint bottle of whisky was three and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there many whisky drinkers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, yes. Yes, you'd - they used to have their - whisky with a glass with a - in a pub I'm talking about now - with a - a glass stem wi
th a - and a ball on the end of it. And - they'd have hot water and sugar put in that to stir it up. They never used to give you a spoon, they used to give you a - a glass stem about as long as that, with a little knob on the end, and the other end was fl
attened out so as you could hold it and stir up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What about meth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305937\charrsid2953716 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 s drinkers and that t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305937\charrsid2953716 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 pe of thing, were there any people like that around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh yes, quite a few of them around. And - they used - if you see any of the - the women come out the 
pub - snivelling they used to say, oh she's had a few gins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I was thinking more of the raw spirits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh methylated - no. No. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 In some parts of the East End that's quite a problem now, people living on that stuff,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It was when 
I was a young man. It could have been about when we were kids because we don't - you don't mix with grown ups like you do when you go to work and I think - but there was meths drink - drinkers when I was in me - sixteen and seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How did you come across them then, at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You hear 'em talk about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That they were drinking this stuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, they - they - yes, or they knew people that did drink it. Or tell you - to have a drop of it. To see what it's like. Well I never have.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But some of the people did drink gin in the pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh plenty, yes. That was a woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305937\charrsid2953716 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 s favourite drink. Gin. Mother's ruin they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They were still drinking it then were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes.
