\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You didn't go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I never went, I never got as far as that, I - misbehaved myself and - I didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Any particular thing that you did or was it just general misbehaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well - I suppose I must have been a - a noted character for being - misbehaving. This particula
r day - there was a - don't know if it was a apple or an orange was thrown out of the class and hit the master's desk and splashed up. But I didn't - I had nothing to do with it and he blamed me you see. And - in the tussle, the - the scrambling to get me
 
out, he hit me in the nose you see and - and - it poured of blood. And I made it - it was worse - as bad as could you see, I smothered it all over me face - and he begged and prayed to me to go to the wash - room to wash it, and I wouldn't. And I didn't. 
And I went home like that. And of course soon as my mother saw it she was up in arms and - said, right, you don't go back to school, I was - just on leaving time it was. You know, fourteen years of age. And I never went back anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That's the end of your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That's how I left school. And - the - the master - schoolteacher was a - only a lit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16597183\charrsid2953716 tle man but he was a little rott}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 er. They all were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 In what particular ways do you think they were bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They had their favourites. And 
those they didn't like well they were the ones that used to - get the cane. And - we had several flights of stairs to climb out of the playground from playtime. And - on each - landing, or section of stairs they'd have a - perfect. And all these prefects 
w
ere - publicans sons or - shopkeepers sons what's nicely dressed with a - nice white - like a collar. Monitors, yes. And they used to the least thing you done you got dragged out you see and then of course you was taken before the master and nothing on ea
r
th would - he would believe you and of course you got - the cane. Well then - used to go out to school and into the playground and play at playtime. And - I suppose there was about - eight of us, used to hold hands - with one boy on a - on his - 'cos them
 
days we used to have blakeys. Blakeys filled up in the bottom of your boots so as you wouldn't wear 'em out. Well they're - they're steel big steel pads. And your parents - father used to bash them in so as you wouldn't wear your - the leather soles out. 
A
nd of course you couldn't half slide with these. And you get eight boys - and one on - sitting down on his haunches holding his hand, you'd swing him round you see, and - we knocked a boy over. And the - of course he felt on his head and got concussion, a
nd - Ellis - ho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16597183\charrsid2953716 w do you pronounce that, erysipela}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
s set in, and he died. And of course my punishment with the eight - seven of these other boy was - we was never out to play any more. And we used to stand - at the master's desk - not the teacher's, the maste
r - at his desk, every playtime, morning and afternoons - with our hands on our heads like that, that'd be about ten minutes. While - while all the other children were out playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 For how many months?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Twelve month. A twelve month. Twelve month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How did you feel when you heard that boy died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh it was shocking. And he was one of our classroom boys, you know, in our own class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And it was just a game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, oh it - a rough game you see they termed it. I can remember - on - on his forehead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But it was played without bad intentions or anything?
