\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, some do, yes. But they didn't in my place, the lady upstairs, she used to spend a lot of t
ime - because - her husband - got drowned during the war. And of course my father was at war so they spent a lot of hours to - with one another, round the table. Chatting and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your father have friends that were particularly his own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, he had a particular circle of friends, but - I wouldn't have known much of them but going to work at the same place I did get to know them but - and which they thought quite a lot of my father, and he did of them, and they often 
used to come - and visit - incidentally, one of my father's pals - I - he was very very friendly with and I used to be taken round to his house when I was a little tiny boy, and I'm still friendly with his son. In fact we're like brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You still see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes, we go - have holidays together don't we, and comes here for weekends. We shall be with him next weekend. And my children call him uncle, they used to but - we've known - we've been friends for years and his - and his father, and his f
ather was an old cockney but he was a - a jolly good old chap. Good hearted old fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You met him when you started going to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And then he worked with me, his father did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 These friends of your father's were mainly people he'd got to know through work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Through their work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would he ever bring them to his home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, occasionally, they would come round, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would he sometimes go to their home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well I can't remember. He used to take me when I was a little boy. A particular - this particular house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What occasions would that be they'd come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Sunday mornings walk out. They'd take - he'd take me round there or they would come and see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Like you were telling me, he'd have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did men and women call on each other as couples, was there much of that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, I - I - I can never remember 'em coming to my place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Not as couples you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. And yet when we were couples we used to go visit. But whether -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It was more the man with his friends and the women with hers do you think then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well it didn't happen at my place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But your mother didn't get to know your father's friends at work wives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, she knew some of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But would they ever go out as a foursome together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No. No, not really, no. No. There - there used to be a nice couple - lived round the corner, name of Roach. They were very friendly with them. And they used to go out foursome together at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Where would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
I believe they used to go - out to a drink anywhere or - well I know they never had holiday together I know. Parties, I've know them to be - go to their parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would they go to a music hall or play ever do you know, or a show of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I don't think so. Pictures. Cinema.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were the friends or relations ever in for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Yes. I can remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would that be family more than friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Friends as well, yes, and - yes, I've
 known 'em - I can remember 'em sitting there having - Saturday night supper. After been playing cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would the Saturday night supper and cards be an arranged thing and they'd be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, it - it would develop. You see? They'd come in on t
he Saturday - evening and they'd sit and play cards and then - when it was finished, there was a supper laid on I can remember that. Next door to you I can remember 'em doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would you have some of the supper too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, I - I was there - must have been to remember it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you remember when you were a child being aware that there were different classes of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How do you remember thinking about it then, what did you think the different classes were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well I used to - I've seen it in the papers, and we - we weren't allowed to read 'em really but we used - I used to read the paper. And - I - well I - used to think that the upper class people had - it - it shouldn't exist. To my mind. Why should -
 they have a lot of money and we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And they had such an awful lot more those days didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It was - crikey, yes, I say they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you think of the world as being sort of two classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No. No, all I knew that we were poor and that was - that was to it. Poor and rich, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You mentioned that at school the monitors tended to be the publicans' sons and the tradesmen's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you think they were favoured at the school generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Definitely, oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, they were. There's no -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they live in your street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 There weren't trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16597183\charrsid2953716 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 people living in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no, wherever the - the trade shops would be on - Barking Road or - big public houses or anything like th
at. Oh yes. And - one particular boy was a - schoolmistress' son. See, another one got favouritism. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you think of the families of those children as being a different class from yourself at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well I did, yes, I thought they were - a - much above us. Yes. And wished I could be the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you think of them as the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, never struck me as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They were another group you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Because - we always had a - a few coppers to spend. I can a
lways go - remember going home from school, an old lady would come at the door. I knew her - in my grandmother's road, and - call me over and I'd go and get her pint of porter - at the off licence, and come back again, and I always got a ha'penny for that
.
 Which was a lot. And then my mother had a younger brother, was - bachelor and of course - he was a postman and he used to - treat me all right. Plus my - other little job I meant to have told you - my old grandfather was crippled so he couldn't bend. And
 I used to have to go round there, didn't have to, but I used to go round there Sunday mornings, and wash his toes - for a shilling. Shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was quite good money then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes - it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He must have been a generous person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes. Oh yes I'd go and do the - 'course the old chap would - must have been retired then and I'd go and call in and get his Friars Balsam at the chemist and what have you, always get a - a penny. Penny and a drop of his lemonade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you were a boy were there certain people you had to call sir, were you brought up to call some people sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, only the school - masters and - people like that, but - ordinary people, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What about your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16597183\charrsid2953716 No, always called him g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 randad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, well might say yes sir or thank you sir or something like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you ever remember anybody being a bit annoyed because you didn't call them sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were you supposed to touch your cap or anything like - that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Or raise it. Always took your cap off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Round where you lived you mentioned there was a Reverend Barney I think his name was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Varney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He was generally quite as well known person was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He was a well know
n - character with - he'd help anybody or - help any waif and stay and all the old children, he used to spend his money and give 'em sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would you call him sir if you met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, he was a great old fellow, he was. Great old chap. Everybody respected him, the roughest of the rough respected him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well he was so kind. And he was so small. Yes. But so kind. And gentle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He treated every body well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Everybody on an equal, yes. Great man he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there any other people who were sort of well known in the area, just well known characters of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well the only ones I - I think told you was - one - a well known character in - in that area was - an old fellow called - Peggy
. Yes. He - he'd get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16597183\charrsid2953716  drunk in a pub and - and once P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
eggy go upset this leg come off and - and he'd stand with his back to the wall and slash and nobody could get near him, police or anybody. And then there was another police - and there was a particular po
liceman was a well known character in - in the force round there was called - Blackmuzzle. Big black moustache. And - when the dock strike was on - big dock strike - they used to fetch all the meat vans - the meat vans out 'cos the meat vans were like ins
u
lating vans - with their pair of horses, and they used to be - either one or two policemen sitting on top of this meat van. And to everybody's delight - this - one of these - they used to turn 'em over. Even them days, used to turn 'em over. Turn the vans
 
over. Turn these - these vans - this van over and - one of 'em fell on - Blackmuzzle's legs, so that was the finish of him. Crippled him - to everybody's delight. 'Cos he was a - a wicked man. Oh well, hard, yes, very hard. Tough. He'd bash anybody that -
 he thought he would take in. Women as well I've seen him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 With his hand or his gloves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He used - well - no, with his hand and glove, yes, give 'em a real - I've - I've seen 'em have him down too and his helmet knocked off.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 By women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, couple of women, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were those women who were drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well, not that - that - they might have been on drink but the particular spot where I saw this was - outside of a paper shop. And - they were trying to - he was trying to - pinch - t
ake this fellow, and he was - well he was really paying him and these two women got stuck into him, they - the evidently knew the man. But of course they all come of worse in the end 'cos he blew his whistle you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And other police came along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes. And fetched this little - stretcher on wheels. And strapped 'em with - strapped him in there and away he went. That used to be a common sight. See that being walked in the road - down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 A little stretcher on wheels to carry people off was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, if you got obstreperous you know, or drunk or anything they would - fetch - have this fetched out from the station. Canvas wasn't it, with a hood. Oh yes. With a hood. And - they used to bundle 'em in there and strap 'em all down, legs 
and everything. Then pull the hood over so as nobody could see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When last do you think you saw that, one of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well I suppose when we - went to work, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I wonder if they still use them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No they've got what they call the hurry up wagons now haven't they you see. These vans that go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 The Black Maria?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, the Black Maria used to be the - the - the van that used to come to the station on a Monday morning - and pick up all the drunks to take 'em to the - We
st Ham Police Court to be - fined - charged. And if you could run behind the - the - the police - the police van, it had two little windows at the back with bars up didn't it, you'd seem 'em going like that to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Any other important people around, what about the doctor, was he well known?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did he live a long way off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, one - one - one - particular doctor, family doctor was a great old chap. The name of Doctor Boyd. He used to go round in his carriage. And the - coachman o
n his seat in the front. And - when we lived in Beckton Road - in the flat upstairs, he used to say, come on Freddie, help me up the stairs. 'Cos he was getting on. But he was a - great old doctor he was. And - I had him I think up 'til when I - just befo
re I went to work, before he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was he there when your brothers and sister were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Yes, he done - he was - all the confinements - Doctor Boyd did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would you say that your mother and father had the same outlook about other social c
lasses, did they treat people in the same way, would they have the same attitude to saying sir to certain people or was your mother perhaps a little more inclined to look to people or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You were saying about your brother in the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, well - he - he didn't care for - for nobody or anything and I can remember the times when - and I was a big boy to him. And - when we were in the playground - there was no facilities to go and get a drink of water normally yo
u - had the tap outside in the playground - with one of these old - iron things, with a steel cup, and when the summertime's on and it's - you're thirsty, you'd have to line up. But my brother wouldn't line up. And - I'd have to go and tell him and I was 
f
ive years older than him, that I wanted a drink and he'd just go up and I'd go at the head of all the crown and - here you are, give my brother a drink, he wants a drink as well. And - demand - forfeits off of 'em such as piggy backs. Piggy back him down 
the playground. And a that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And they'd give it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, 'cos they were scared of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What would he do to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He'd - he - he'd - he'd pick a fight on 'em, you see. And if he decided he'd have a - and he'd go round on -
 on this other boy's back waving his hands around and - you know, everybody - all the kiddies are looking at him. And then he'd say, right too, that's enough. And if he decide somebody else'll give him a - piggy back he'd go up and demand it. And they'd b
e scared to refuse him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did he have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes he's lovely boy when he - he went to work, he - he - it's just these boys - pranks. Yes. Oh he was a terror.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you and he fight much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh yes. Yes, we used to fight terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 With your fists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes. Yes. I bashed him. I - I've got him and bashed his head on the floor. Right up 'til - oh - we were both out to work - when we used to fight. But it - we used to lead my mother a life that did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 She didn't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, and she used to - with me being the eldest I used to - take a lot off of him 'til I couldn't take any more and then I'd decide I'd - I'd have a go, but - she stopped me because - my mother was - she'd get - pushed - get into you if she wanted
 to. And - she's had me pinned up on the wall. When I've been going out to meet Mrs Kent. And I've decided I'd drop it and forget it because - we were going to go outside and fight. But of course we had no father then, he was dead. And she said, if you go
 out there and fight I'll throw this can of milk over you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So you were still fighting 'til you were quite old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, - well - up to about sixteen. You see, 'cos they used to look upon me as the as the - my mother made me the - master of the hou
se you see, everything - she used to say to the children they'd tell me. And I used to try and keep 'em in line. And you know what - fashions are, that particular time - Oxford bags came out, and that was - trousers something like about - yes, twelve inch
es - twenty-four inches round. And he bought these, and I made him go back and change 'em. When he bought himself a pair of shoes - the new shoes was designed with a - huge great toe on - come up like a big bump, they called 'em \endash 
 bull-nose - bulldog nosed 
shoes. And I complained about it to him, you know, told him he'd no business to buy these sort of things. He was putting a pair of rubbers on. And - the gimlet what was boring it - he'd broken it and he asked me to get it out for him, and I got it in the 
-
 getting it out and it hit the back of a chair. Oh my goodness, there was holy ructions over it. He swore blind I done it for the purpose and - come on outside and we'll settle it. I said, right, I've had enough of you. And that - that was the particular 
time with the - with the milk. So I decided I'd - I'd cut it out and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You didn't after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No. Oh he was a terror. But - of course after that we - you see, the five years made a - it was a great difference. And him and the other one only had 
two so they were bosom pals you see. But of course we are now, we're - we're - well we were before we were married, we - we - we grew out of it. And he admits, you know, if he's ever talking, what a - what a - beast he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Is he married too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, he's married. Yes, he comes here and sees us, he - quite a nice fellow but a real cockney. He is a real Cockney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you say a real Cockney what exactly do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well, he's - he's not particular how he expresses himself you see, he'll
 say - Gor' blimey this - and - bleeding that and - you see and - I don't use a lot of that, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you give it up a long time ago, presumably people spoke like that when you were a child did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you give it up when you were quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh well I - I - I don't say I don't swear but - I don't express myself - all the time like that but he will. But he seems to get away with it. You know what I mean, it doesn't matter what company he's in - he's always the sam
e and he seems to get away with it, he's got a way with him that - everybody laughs. We've been on a - to - Austria - 'cos he isn't short of money, and - he'd like to go him and his wife, and we went on a coach tour. And the expressions of all that and yo
u - you know you get a mixture of people in a coach, some have got - a bit churchy, some are very - la-di-dah, but - Reggie was a very popular fellow in there, they all used to laugh at him, it was the - the Cockney expressions and the Cockney slang.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 People love it don't you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And my two daughters always introduce him to their friends as their religious uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was there more swearing and slang and things than there is now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your parents ever use the rhyming slang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. They never used to swear a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they use the rhyming slang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, you mean apples and pears and - bird lime and - yes, and - that's right. Billy and Dick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Not very well. Yes, Billy and Dick, you see, not sick. That - that's an expression that - well we'd say, oh he's Billy and Dick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you remember your parents using this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, they didn't use it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But some people did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, it was used at - in the works. Oh yes. Right u
p 'til - late - late in years it's - you'll often get a chap say, what's the bird lime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What's bird lime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was there a rather different sort of language at work from what people used at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, it's - there's a lot of it goes on now, I use quite a bit of I where I work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 The rhyming slang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 For the boys, you know, they - 'course they get me on it at times but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It's a bit new to the Essex people is it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And they like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh of course they do, yes. They call me Cockney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 At what stage in your life do you think you began to feel youawanted a different life for yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When I went - shortly after I left school, went to work. I vowed and declared I'd never stay in tha
t - quarter, not with the little old back garden - or yard. I mean - your - your young days were spoilt, you - you couldn't do anything. Only play out in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But surely when you were a boy that didn't worry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not at school. No, bu
t with - once I went out to work and - and started to see things - because - and I wasn't - I wasn't - mixed with a bad gang but it didn't matter where you go, you - you - if you wasn't careful you got involved. I got a beating up one Sunday evening - for
 
nothing. And I'm - dressed up in me best clothes. And these sports and pastimes shops where you could go in and - fire a few rifles and - go on machines. And - fellow I was with was in there and he was a crack shot. And we were dressed, them days, what - 
a
 lot weren't around that quarter, had - we had bowler hats on. And - this chap was knocking the - firing at these balls and knocking them down and every time he knocked one down these fellows was bashing him on the - head with - with his bowler hat you se
e
 and was bashing it in. And I don't know anything about it. And he came out to me and he said, hold tight Fred, there's going to be trouble here. I said, why, what's the matter? And Before I had time - bosh, crash and I'm - I go to run and I slid over and
 - dragged all the backside of me trousers out, and had me bowler hat bashed in. Then another time an old boy hit me on the head with a stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You must have asked for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I didn't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was it rather high classed to wear a bowler hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
When my father - took me in to buy a hat - go and buy a trilby hat, I said, well - if buy it I'm not going out wearing it. And he took me out on Sunday morning, and walked me all round Canning Town with this hat on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 To show you off sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, and broke me in though. And from that day - I was - dressed, and they used to call me - the Duke of Kent. Yes, that's what - he's left it on, he - the Duke of Kent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did people behave differently towards you depending on the clothes you wore at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716  you was a bit of a - bit of a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 issy boy if you was - respectably dressed. But eventually - and I lived in Canning Town when I finished up wearing - all types of - I - I bought a - grey velour once. You - you wasn't with me the
n. Spats, walking stick. And nobody used to - I brazened it out and nobody used to take any notice of me afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 There'd be some people who'd think you were soft like that and might attack you, but were there other people who might treat you with 
more respect, say in a shop if you were dressed like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well yes, I suppose so. I know my aunts used to say I used to - what they liked about me, I had - dressed as - like a gentleman. That used to make me smile. And then I used to go to a - a the
atre - was a well known - really a well known - well it got a good - bad reputation this theatre, but I used to go in there and - and sing - turns, good shows for tuppence - on the stage. Not a picture palace. A theatre. No, imperial Palace. It was called
. Really good shows, good -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were those plays or sort of variety turns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Variety turns, such as Hetty King and - and all them type of people - male impersonators. All for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your wife go to any of those places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Not before I to
ok her. Used to have a - I think it was tuppence to go in but if you liked to pay - an extra penny and they called it early doors, you went in first. And you got the front seats. No, I used to go there - quite a lot. Quite a lot. It was rough in there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was it after the first war that you started going out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You were in your twenties by then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Eighteen. Eighteen or nineteen. We got married on - three pounds - three a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Combined?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. My wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That wasn't too bad for then was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh I had a good job. No, you couldn't get houses, we paid fourteen shillings a week for two rooms. No, I can - I consider that - I've had a very lucky life. Good life. Always had a good job, I kept it, I got a go
od job and I kept it, I worked hard and I kept it. For the same firm. And I always got good money, I think when I was eighteen - I was earning fifty shillings a week. Including a week's holiday with pay. But that was a union rule. The Transport and Genera
l
 Workers Union that I joined - I was getting eight - twenty-two pound ten a week, and - I joined the union and within a week my money - my money was made - three pound a week. Fifty shillings a week when I - joined the union when I was eighteen. And - imm
e
diately I joined the union I got - my money was raised to three guineas a week. With a week's holiday with pay. That'd be somewhere round about 1919. And of course plenty of overtime. As - as you should be paid, but mind you I done a lot of hours. I used 
to go - I - I can remember one particular period that I was up at - went to work Sunday evening at twelve o'clock. And got two hours break in each - night up to the Thursday. No. And follow that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were you driving all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I wasn't driving then, I was mating. But driver was with me. And - I fell over - cut me face didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You fell over, from exhaustion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Must have - no, I must have - shut me eyes and fell asleep. And that was two o'clock on a Thursday lunch time. They took me 
home by car - and - I was back again at twelve at night, again that night 'til the Sunday. But I didn't mind, I was earning the money and - I - I - I - never used to worry about it at all. It wasn't sweated labour. She was only courting then. But when we 
were married she said, that's terrible amount of hours on her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there no regulations then against it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What happened if you'd refused?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh well that would be just - you refused and that's all there was to it. But I was
 paid for it and that was all I was concerned, as long as I was earning money. And I wasn't earning money - the poor way, I mean I was - got me proper dues, I was paid time and a quarter and time and a half and - double time, I mean - it wasn't - wasn't b
ad - bad pay at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was it a bit lonely for your wife sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes, it must have been. I haven't seen my children, I've gone to work on a Monday morning and I haven't seen 'em 'til the Sunday. Following Sunday have I.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You didn't have a lot of money worries then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, we didn't have a lot to throw away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But it wasn't something that was pressingly worrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well, this might - this might - interest you. Our deposit on the house then was thirty pounds. A - deluxe model we c
hose and we paid thirty-five pounds deposit. And that was a - a - thirty what? No, no, thirty - when was the war - '39 - '37, we lived there two years when war come along. Might have been. That's right. Yes. Yes. To what young couples have to pay today - 
five seven five, five seventy-five. Fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
er hundred and seventy-five. And now they're asking - same house - seven thousand pounds. It's all out of proportion isn't it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
nd you you they're lovely houses, it was - it's a house that - that'll never get old because it's got a - one big lounge right through, even them days. What they call a sun trapped house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It's terrible for young people today starting off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh, shocking. I mean what - what ordinary - fellow or couple can find seven thousand pound?
 Well - they don't find it, they've got to find about two haven't they. And that wasn't some finding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You mentioned doing your grandfather's toes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, for a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And getting a pint of porter for an old lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there any other jobs that you had fairly regularly for getting money while you were still a pupil at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No. No, they were only just - just those little errands and - well, good deeds for me old grandfather but of course naturally knew I was - going to get money for it. Such as - tuppence, I was never - it was very very rare - less than tuppence off of him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But no delivery boy jobs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did other boys have them or wasn't there much going in that line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, there wasn't much - to do them days at all because - people didn't have papers - delivered much then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Your first full time job was at your father's own firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh - interrupting you, there was - you used to get schoolboys going round the streets in the
 evening calling out - Star - paper Star, and people used to open their doors and go out and pay for their paper, and the paper was - ha'penny then. They used to do a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And - the man - a man used to employ them off of 
a - main street somewhere and give them a - I think it was called a quire which con - constituted twenty-five papers. And if they sold those twenty-five papers - they would get the large sum of a penny - penny for that. And he would get the other, the res
t of the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So it was quite hard work for not much return?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you ever feel attracted to doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, my - my parents or my father wouldn't allow such a thing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Why was that, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well I suppo
se he thought it was - be - bit degrading or - something like that, 'cos they were very very poor, these boys that used to do it. Plus that - they were little gangs you know introduced to this paper man that - dished them out with bundles of papers and th
ey would take - I believe they used to have to buy the papers off of him. First before they - sold them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So if they had a very bad night for any reason then they would be down on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Quite a tough job for young lads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh it was them days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Your first job was at Moreland and Haynes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No. The first - no, the first job - I required - I got myself in a little small rubber factory in Custom House. Making - beer stop - stoppers and - of course they went onto the war and they
 were making ebonite rings for the submarines, and all that sort of thing and I used to have to - cut these rings - and - one particular time I remember they wanted somebody to work all night. And I spoke to my mother about it and she agreed for me to do 
it and I worked all night and I got seven shillings for that. I can remember that so well because with that seven shillings I went and bought myself a watch.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 A new watch was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, a new watch out of a jewellers for seven shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How did it go, did it go all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes. I had that watch up 'til - oh - when I was about seventeen. And I used to go out to these parties and - drop this watch and kick it 'cos I was a well known character for - acting about you see. I've done that 
all my life - entertaining - parties and things like that, and that used to be one of my gimmicks. And this watch - never did fail. It - it used to go all the time. Yes, it was I - I kicked it across the room and then we've - I've picked it up and - hande
d it r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 und and it still - went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you do conjuring and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, no conjuring, no, just - acting the fool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So in that job you once had to work all night, was that exceptional?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was an exceptional, yes. I had that fo
r - eight months. And - I had a accident there - with some white metal that - blew into me eyes and from then on my mother wouldn't - allow me to go to work there anymore. It was too dangerous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you think the safety precautions were not all they should have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no. No. No, because - I used to - do all types of work, anything to get extra money, and - what they called a greasers job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Now a greasers job used to be a man goes round with oil can and grease, and oil the 
machines and - them days they used to have great big shafts running - bolted to the wall, with pulleys spinning round, with belts down onto the machine, you see. And they drove the machines. And I used to have to climb up there and - tie me jacket up with
 
rope, so - and sleeves with string so that I wouldn't - have anything hanging because if once you got caught on the shaft it would - damage your - well, break your arm or anything like that you see. But I done all that sort of thing to get extra - money. 
And them days - things was very very - crude, because - these machines, they used to - mix powder up and all other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 concoctions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
, and put 'em into the rollers and that - hot - rollers were heated up inside with steam, and they used to keep going round and the
n it would form into a rubber, and then they used to cut that across and roll it back and there was one particular fellow there that - was blind with one eye. He came out of the orphan school he - was an orphan, and I used to - be friend him because they 
u
sed to call him - Nelson and all this you see and the chap was very - inoffensive. And this rubber came over and dropped onto his arms and being all - sticky and - and - this sticky substance, dragged his hands into the rollers and he lost both those arms
 up to his shoulders. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you see that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, I never saw that happen, no. But I had - I used to go and speak to him and we had a market place in - Canning Town, called Rathbone Street. And he opened a stall down there. But however he
 used to manage I do not know because then he - he never had no artificial limbs. And the thing was that - he used to like a cigarette but of course he had - to have - cigarette in his mouth all the time. And it was a - a terrible - affair, but that's how
 things were, so - crude and neglected - for safety first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How many people worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh I suppose about - it was only a very small place, I should imagine about two hundred people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Who was running the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well it was called the Climax - Stopper Company them days. But who - who the owners were I never did know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But who was sort of over you in your particular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh I had a foreman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh he was quite - very nice. Oh yes, and matter
 of fact I had one or two overseers but they were all quite nice. I was happy at me job there. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What about the other people, how did you get on with them at work in your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 All right. The girls - I used to get on very well with th
e girls, girls about sixteen. Used to put the rings on the stoppers and all this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were there more young girls there than young boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh - yes. Yes. Yes, there was more young girls than there was young boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Some people ha
ve told me that when they started work quite young there was quite a lot of fun and games really and larking about, was that the case there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh yes, there was quite a lot of that going about there, that's how it was I got blind - with this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 tal went into my eyes was through playing about. You see, not enough precautions or - overseers to look - look after you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What sort of hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I think I used to start at - half past seven 'til six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And Saturday morning would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, Saturday mornings, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But no work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you went there did they say you could have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no. No, no holidays with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was only when you got that other job and joined the union that you got holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Then I - well as I say, my mother made me leave it, we decided between us - 'cos my father was at the war. And he didn't want me to go and work where he worked because it was so - well - rough - c
rude - and tough. Because you were exposed to all weathers. And - no ladies worked in there at all, it was all men labour. And - it was a real tough job. And I used to start then at half past six in the morning 'til - half past five. Half hour for breakfa
st in the morning between - half past eight and nine. And lunch was from - one 'til quarter to two. Three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
quarters of an hour for lunch. No tea breaks. Or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Straight on from quarter to two until you knocked off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Which was what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When - when I left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you finished the end of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Quarter to - half past five. And toilets - toilets - only had little tiny doors. Just sufficiently to - to cover you you know from - decency so - they could see the top and the bottoms, and they knew how long -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So there was no going for a smoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh no, no, because it used to - bellow out you see and - and the toilets was exposed to the whole of the - place. It wasn't - screened of at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You only really went there you say because your father was at the war and couldn't stop you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Well I took a letter you see there and immediately they - gave me a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Because of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And I started at thirteen and six a week. With two shillings a week war bonus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You would then have been about fifteen or sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Fifteen then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So that was very good money for a fifteen year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What did you get in the way of money in you first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Eight shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was always the same except for that one time you got the extra seven shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you said that there were no ladies working there, do you think if there are women working at a place it's less rough, do you t
hink it makes people less rough in their was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh - well yes, because - the whole atmosphere was, you see, men had worked - with theirselves so many years that - that the - language and the - crude way they went on, it did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 n't}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716  - it wasn't a fit place f
or a woman. But - towards the end of the first world war - we did have women - they had to employ women to come in and - what they call drillers, on drilling machines. And - they were pretty local women, that got husbands in the war and what have you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did that make a difference do you think to the language and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh - well - I suppose so to a certain extent but then you - we - we - I found that women was nearly as - that - that type of woman was nearly as bad as the men. 'Cos as I say you'd got to be tough, and if you wasn't tough -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 In that first job you say you were a greaser, but you did other jobs in that first job as well didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I was really, I used to - cut these rings, that was my - on a - on a lathe. Was my - really my - principle job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What was your principle job when you started at Moreland and Haynes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 A rivet carrier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Can you tell me what that involved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well that involved - you used to have a furnace - where you put - so many rivets i
nto the furnace in sections - and - we used to - make these trusses or - frames for buildings or - principle thing then was - aerodromes. Aerodrome hangars and - when the rivets was correctly hot we used to have - I used to have to pick 'em out with the g
o
ngs and throw 'em to where they were working. You see? It was quite an interesting job because - you throw 'em to a certain degree so as they - they caught them - in the - in the - in the pliers, in tongs. I'd have long tongs, they'd have short ones. And 
they'd catch them. And then put that into the hole of a - whatever they were - and this machine would close together and - make a rivet you see and joint it. That was before welding ever come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And you were doing that all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no, no, I - I went from there to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But when you were doing that you were doing that all day long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
All - all day long. Yes, it was quite a - quite a easy job you see because you - put your rivets into the - into the furnace and then you had a quarter of a
n hour or so to wait - while they got hot. You might do other little tiny jobs but nothing - you just - and you wasn't guilty of standing about because you was waiting for your - the particular rivets to get hot you see. And at the side of this machine, t
h
is furnace - we used to - we make - made all these implements ourselves, was a iron oven. And the men used to fetch their dinners - such as - chops and what have you, in a - in a dinner cooked over night at home, fetched them in the morning in a plate and
 I used to have to put them all in this oven - and get 'em hot for 'em. So as when it was lunchtime they come and get their dinners out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they give you anything for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not that particular - time, but prior to that they used - I was a - a tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 boy there. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Before you started doing the rivet carrying you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Yes, before I was tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12916145\charrsid2953716 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 boy. I used to have to go right round the works - collect all these - pint - cans, they were really beer cans. But they used to buy them new,
 they were tuppence each, and - they fetched them into work and they'd either put a bit of wire on or - mark 'em somehow or other with their name, and used to collect them, we used to have a long stick - about - eight foot long, with all nails on them, so
 
as you hung your cans - on those - on that stick. And - men used to fetch in - tea, sugar and a - and a batch of - condensed milk, and pour it in - on there, at home this would be done, and made a little package of it. So you got each one of them'd give y
o
u those, and you dropped that in the tin. Then you'd go down to the furnaces - and fill your cans up with water. Put 'em on the furnace on the plate, you had a huge great hook, and as they boiled you took 'em of and tipped these batches of tea in. And as 
you made your quota, there was two or three of us doing it, as you made your quota - then you took 'em all back to 'em you see. To - drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they have anything to eat with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, they'd have their bit of lunch. 'Cos -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But you didn't have to see after that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, yes, I used to have to do that - for that. Then I used to have to go round for lunch, and some would want fish and chips. And cheese with - you'd get a - I used to get a quarter of cheese for tuppence, a pennorth 
of bread and - ha'porth of pickles in a - in a little cardboard paper and the fish and chips. Well all the fish and chips I used to buy - some people would have a - give you a good price, some would want sixpence for their lunch, others would want three}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid728259\charrsid2953716  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 pence and four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid728259\charrsid2953716  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
pence. You go into the fish shop, he knew you you see, and he's day, well there's your lunch. You got one for nothing. For taking the business in there. And I'd go next door and buy a - newspaper and then I'd come out and go near the works and
 we used to have a big - board fence on the pavement and alay all the lunches out and I'd make two or three - buckshee dinners there. Buckshee dinners you know, free dinners, extra, and I'd sell them. And I used to make a - my - extra money on that busine
ss. Then on a Saturday they used to come along, you'd go and make their tea and then they'd give you their three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid728259\charrsid2953716  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
pence or whatever it is for making their tea all the week. It was quite a good job. I earnt more money doing that than I did when I was rivet carrying, when I was taken off of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I always thought tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid728259\charrsid2953716 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 boy work was quite poorly paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh no, I got - no, I was getting that thirteen and six a week and I - I - I used to get somewhere round about - seven or eight shillings a week for that, making tea. From the tips, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So that was quite good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh it was quite good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was all you did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Oh I - I'd have me own little job to go to on a - what they called a - a - a bending machine but - that was just to fill the time up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You were really mainly employed in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Employed for taking - making tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you run other errands for them like buy them cigarettes?
