e particular character there, 'course caps were worn them days you see - at work, yes, 'cos you was out in the open. And this particular man - he used to make a cigarette - last him - all the morning and one all the afternoon. And - rigidly he'd take his 
c
ap off and they used to drop their cigarette in the peak of their cap you see. This was a regular thing. But this was a particular man that - that was a note - noted character for this. Take his cigarette out, had two draws. Pinch it out, take his cap off
, put it back on his head again. And that - he - he done that all the time I worked there, for years and years. 'Til he retired. And it was the same habit every day. Two draws - nip it out, and put it back.
