cular foreman, he - he caught me sitting on a - he caught me asleep once. And - well - to be honest it was - we were up what they called - put into the stores to do tidying up, and - three or four - of us lads, we bashed a hole through the wall, and when 
w
e got through this hole in the wall it went into a park. And - a recreation ground presented by - Lyles the sugar people, to Silvertown - people you see. And we climbed through this hole, and go and swim in the Thames. And we were swimming in the Thames o
ne days - one afternoon and - the looker out - chaps - put his head through the hole in the wall and said, look out, Fred Self coming along. That was the foreman. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14752863\charrsid2953716 scampered}{\rtlch\fcs1 
