anaging director sent for me - and he thanked me for what I'd done. And I said, well I couldn't very well - he said, you done the right thing. I was paid for what I done, the hours. But - I made that decision, I - I said to the other staff, well I'll take
 
him home. Get him home for you, and I took him to the hospital, that was at Woolwich. And things like that, they did really look after - he - he was a - a good boss. If you were ill - such as - T.B. and you had to go away for six to eight months or twelve
 months, I know one particular fellow, and he got his pay all the time he was away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh this is the later - well - oh he was a staff man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 An ordinary worker wouldn't have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, ordinary worker wouldn't have got i
t. But my father - he came back from the first world war - as you know, I told you, he was gassed - and - this was the first manager, came out to him -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7415895\charrsid2953716  they put him on the wharf \endash  so }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 as he'd get plenty of - fresh air you see off the river. And he said to h
im - have you had a holiday, since you've been out of the Army Kent? So he said, no sir. Oh well, he said, then you - you talk yourself off a week, get - get yourself to the seaside and you'll get paid for it. And they did - he did do that. Plus they did 
p
ay my mother out religiously every week to the - he came home - with half pay. 'Cos that was what the firms were doing in 1914/18 war, they - to encourage chaps to go into the forces they used to say well we'll give you half pay, half your money, towards 
your army allowance. And my mother got that right up 'til - my father was discharged out the Army. It was a family - family firm and it was a jolly good firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How did you get your very first job in the rubber firm, did you find it for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 L
abour Exchange. No, I could have gone into the engineers but you see it was like everything else when you first leave school - you want to rush off and earn money. And I wouldn't wait. I was going to be spoke for in - to go into an engineering firm but I 
wouldn't wait. Then - after I got this job from the Labour Exchange, they came after me and I - I - I - wouldn't give in, you see, I'd got this job and I wasn't going to lose it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did anybody teach you anything before you went to school, like reading or writing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, well I went to school when I was three. Yes. No, because I was so young when went to school - I - I can't hardly remember the reason why, but I remember being take to school by my uncle. My mother's young brother. And he took me to the 
wrong school. And I knew I was in the wrong school - I - I could - feel it. I didn't know anybody. And when the playtime come along I run home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Even at that age you'd expect to see familiar people around you you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Where did he take you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well - I - I had to go to Beckton Road school and the - and the other school he took me to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7415895\charrsid2953716 was - Beckton Road but up - Hol}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 born Road, about another mile away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So what did your mother do then when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh I forget now, I
 can't remember but - strangely enough I - I can never - wonder why the teacher didn't query why I was there. 'Cos I sat in - I can remember sitting in the classroom. And I knew I was lost, I - I - I didn't know anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And you were only three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was that pretty general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Definitely it was. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And all day too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Used to come home and then go back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was a board school, it wasn't a fee paying school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was it mixed in the infants and then boys and girls separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Mixed in - in the infants and then the boys and girls, it was a three storey school this one - so the girls was in - the infants was on the ground floor, the girls was on the second floor and the boys was 
on the top floor. And you used to have to go up these - spiral staircase, only like big ones, and - on each platform there'd be a - perfect - monitor. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 From the kind of better off families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That's right, well - the favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you move from the school in Beckton Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I - I - all the time, that was the only school I went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you always walk to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 About how long would that take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you first went when you were a very little boy did you go alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Alone. No, alone. I went alone, I - I - there's a - an instance I can tell you - I think I was about - I must have been thirteen, 'cos I suppose I'm get - getting quite a big lad - know my father was at the war, wel
l he hadn't gone out to France then. And I put his boots on, 'cos - whacking great boots they were to go - scrub the yard. And I run a needle - right up me heel. Straight up there. And of course when I put it on the ground I couldn't. I said to me mother,
 
I've got a needle up my heel. Oh well, she said - you - go to Popular hospital. And I went to Popular hospital on my own. And - they freezed it - and as far as I could see afterwards when I had a look they had cut diamond shape and they got these four pie
c
es of needle out. It had broken. In four. And of course when I - this was on the Saturday - morning. And on the Saturday lunchtime - my father had walked - from Tilbury - there was a big Army camp there then - Purfleet. He'd walked to Barking, he couldn't
 
train it because of the redcaps you see. He'd walked from Tilbury to Barking, caught the tram, and come home for a - weekend leave, you know, unknown. In kitchener's blue. Because they couldn't supply khaki, they never had - sufficient khaki to go so he s
aid - they put 'em in blue serge suits. Looked like a Salvation Army captain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was that quite a usual thing to go to a hospital if you got some serious injury, rather than call a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes. You had to pay them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And you got that free at the hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes. Yes, got it free and you was accepted and taken in as if you - you now - really looked after. There was no waiting and - and - stuck there all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You said you used to get these canings when you were late after ta
king your father's dinner along, were the teachers very particular about any other things, they seem to have been quite harsh really from what you tell me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh they were harsh. They had a favourite habit of giving a - you know, right - with their flat hand. A lot of that went on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What sort of things were they particularly concerned about in the way of behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well, talking and - eating sweets. Anything like that, you couldn't - and - and you couldn't go to the toilet too many times neither.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They'd get suspicious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes. And you - I was never asked but then they had - different ones out of the class - to go up to the kitchen and cook their dinner. Peel potatoes and cabbage and and - then go up there at half past - two and wash up for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Out of school time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What about tidiness, were they fussy about how your clothes looked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And whether you - were clean and neat, they weren't worried about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. 'Cos I had boys in my class with no shoes and boots on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 And the teachers didn't worry about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did they try to help any of these very hard up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not that I can - ever remember, no. No, I don't - I can't remember 'em - that - far as I could say th
at they wasn't - they just didn't - wasn't interested. If you went to work - if you went to school nicely dressed and - and was just so so well you was - you was all right, you was one of the - favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But if your parents couldn't afford it they weren't prepared to help in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, if - you could - no, oh no. No, they were bullies. No doubt about it - in the big boys, I'm not saying - so much in the infants 'cos - you don't sort of remember so much there but - I can remember the - the - t
he bullying that used to go on and the fights and the - the bashing and the - lay you across the table - I never had it but they have done with 'em, and - and caned their backsides. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did the monitors do caning as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, only the - only the teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you ever remember any rough music round where you lived, anybody having a terrific noise made outside their house with pots and pans?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well - only - what Mrs Kent said about the New Year. But - when I was on the wagon of cour
se - the - at seventeen years of age we used to have cut all round the back chats you see because it was quite a good walk to work. And - they were - hell of a lot of blacks - in Custom House. And they used to be huge great fellows and all their rings and
 
- big cigars on, and they all went in to work in Lyles - Tate Y Lyles and they used to on a Sunday night - if I was going to work at two or three in the morning, walking round or bike - cycling round, they'd have parties on and it was nothing to see all t
h
e windows smashed. Where other people - had - have had so much of it that they've gone out and smashed their windows in. Yes, where the blacks were see. With white women, not - all black and black women. 'Cos there wasn't - wasn't any black women over her
e them days. But they used to be huge great big fellows and 'course - always had the appearance of having plenty of money, whether they did or not I don't know. But the - the - these - parties that used to create and go on all night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What roads did they live in then, did they live quite near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Yes, this was round - yes, this was near Russell Road school. Not Russell Road, Frederick Road school. Round - just round that back part. There was about four - four roads. Run off near the Dock Road. Ne
ar the docks. And there was all - all these - not all, but - they'd be - two or three parties in one road going. And the majority - I - if you walked round through there on a Sunday afternoon well they'd all be at the door, there - there'd be half of 'em 
would be black men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 I wonder what jobs they did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Worked in Tate and - oh they only had - in Tate Y Ly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7415895\charrsid2953716 le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 s - but they only had - the jobs what the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7415895\charrsid2953716 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716  white}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7415895\charrsid2953716  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 men wouldn't do. 'Cos we could come - you used to see 'em going home Sunday - Monday mor
ning or any mornings from night work, they used to do all - a lot of night work there too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Night work was very unpopular was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well, yes, it - always has been unpopular, night work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you were a boy your home was rented wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What did you think of your landlord as a family, was he a bad landlord or a good one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well - no, I - I should say he was a bad landlord really, although - probably Mrs Kent can't remember, he was a - he was made - he was a wealthy man.
 He lived in Canning Town, and he had property all over the place and there was a road - named after him. And that was name of Ford. Ford Road. And he - he was a Mr Ford. And he used to walk around in that area - in - tails and ka top hat. Big man. Yes. N
o, Pacific Road. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So he made plenty of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, he never had your houses painted or decorated or done - anything done to it. What - whatever went wrong you had do it yourself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did he collect his own rents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, he had a landlord. A - a - a - an agent, yes, used to go around collecting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 He didn't have anything personally to do with your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, you'd see him walk around and have a look at his property and that's when - he'd be in his top hat - and tails.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When a person appeared like that, dressed very differently, did kids run after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No. Oh no, they were - fairly well - behaved, I suppose it was a sight they were used to him particularly. 'Cos he was a Mr Ford. The landlord.
