\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That's up the top and you sat on forms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Would there be fights and things there sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, hitting one another - on the head with bottles and - what have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Was that not a place you'd take a lady to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, not really. Lot of girls would go but they were as rough as the boys. Quite as rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you started work did you make new friends then? Or did you keep on with the same people you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, I made - new friends - where I - who
 I worked with and - as I tell you, that chap that - who had the one eye, I used to go out a lot with him - in the evenings. But of course he was much older than me too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What sort of places would you go to with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Pictures or - the - Stratfor
d Empire, or - up the Imperial Palace as we called it, but where it was - 'cos we know - I never used to pay tuppence then, I used to go and - have a shilling seat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It was tuppence when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. Was tuppence then when I - I was
 up - oh it might have gone up, I forget. But I know it was definitely tuppence for the - but that was tuppence and the pictures was a penny. For five films. And you sat on a - sat on a form. 'Cos all these little picture palaces that opened were - shops 
that closed and they'd converted them into picture palaces. Little palaces like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were you expected to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 After you had started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 What time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Ten. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you stick to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well I did 'til - as I got older I broke the rules. But - from ever time I can remember it didn't matter what hour I came in - was - 'cos - I used to keep - bad hour at times, but I wasn't in bad company, I used to get involved in card playing. And - 
but I always went into my mother's bedroom, to kiss her goodnight. Yes, didn't matter what time it was. Always. Maybe I'd go in and tell her a tale, you know, what had happened, something like that. And there'd always be my supper on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your parents meet your friends you made at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You'd bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh yes, I'd bring them home. I have brought them home - when my father was - discharged out the Army you couldn't smoke, you see - it didn't - even cook - m
y mother cooking used to choke him. And - if we were having - they were coming round I always gave them their instructions. No cigarette smoking - while you're indoors. And they would abide by it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When would you usually bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Saturday evening or - Sunday evening or one night in the week, I don't - they'd come round for me or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 They'd known Mrs Kent a long time, you didn't have to introduce her I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh no - No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Anything else you particularly rem
ember about your leisure time activities in your teenage years, after leaving school, any big differences in your life or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, only - as I say - going out and about and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Having more money to spend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And - I used to 
dress as - dress as nice as I possibly could. And often I'd go up to - Kingston - on my own - for a weekend with my grandmother and - her daughter. And take a - that would be - be my aunt, but not all that older than me, and take her out to - the Kingston
 Empire. And - well I was really a favourite with all my aunts wasn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Were your other brothers jealous about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No, they just accepted it, I suppose because of the - difference again you see in the years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you started work in your very first job did you give your mother some of that money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes. Yes. I used to - out of that - eight shillings I used - she used to have seven, and I have a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It's wonderful how you remember all these sums of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well yo
u see, there's some things - there's some things - stick in your mind you see, I bought a bicycle - for five shillings. And - you see this is a thing which you can - I can remember - and I - I wanted a pump for this bike, and the cheapes}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9379685\charrsid2953716 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716  to bike pump I co
uld buy was a shilling. And it had got a - handle to it. And I went and bought this - pump, on a Friday night, I was paid on Fridays there, spent me shilling on the - on a pump, and coming home I hung it on me handlebars and the handle slowly said down an
d
 got in the front forks - front wheel of the - of the bike and pulled all the forks out - spokes out. And I couldn't ride me bike for the weekend. And I'd got no money. But it's possible I wouldn't remember but it's possible my mother gave me a shilling b
a
ck or something like - but I know I - I nearly cried me eyes out because - it was me only shilling and I'd - bought - this pump and I'd got to have it or else I - was - running around mump - mumping - pumps to pump me tyres up and - and they wouldn't stop
 up long 'cos they wasn't no good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 How old were you when you got that bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9379685\charrsid2953716 On leav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 ing school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, I bought it off old - old Mr Rand. Five shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did you give her quite a high proportion of the money in your next job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, yes. Yes? And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did she have most of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
No, oh no. No, I - I - I kept a good bit myself. You see, because - through the war - and - the - half pay with the Army - money, she was fairly - for those days was fairly - comfo
rtable then you see. And I was able to - keep quite a bit for myself. And - no, I always had plenty of pocket money - to buy clothes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9379685\charrsid2953716 with and - well I was always buy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 ng different - clothes. And - I remember when my father was ill - in bed - I gave the whole
 of my money up then, 'course I was in me twenties. So as he would no worry about how - how they were going to get on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 So you give up all your pay packet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 All my pay packet money. Not - for a long while but - for a period of time to - try a
nd prevent him from laying in bed, 'cos I knew he was - going to die, I knew that. I had the - the savvy to know that he would - it was impossible for him to live. Although I was never told that, but I knew that. The way he was deteriorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 When you
 were a small child now, you described to me how you had this big bath on Friday nights - can you remember when you'd have a clean set of clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That night. In front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 But they didn't have pyjamas then did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You'd sleep in your underwear?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Under - a shirt, yes, and your underwear. And we'd sleep - three in a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 With your two brothers that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And - 'cos I can remember - one particular period, we was - bitterly cold and we were kids
. And I decided we'd warm the bed up. And I went out in the garden and got three or four bricks, put 'em in the oven, and hotted 'em up. Put 'em in the bed. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You burnt the sheets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, oh - all - all you could get was - oh - ooh - oh. Oh. Se
e, and my mother said, what's going on in there? It was me younger one again you see, the baby brother, he was the one that was getting burnt. Then I had a cousin - came and stayed with us, come from - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9379685\charrsid2953716 Middlesbrough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716  - to London to work and I got him a job 
- at this - rubber factory. And - we went to bed one night - four of us in one bed. And of course we were playing about - and giggling and laughing, my father was in the Army then. And - my mother's threatened to come in there and - cane us. Anyway we kep
t
 on and I decided then that I would - change places with - so we changed places in the bed, with this cousin. Barney we called - he was called. We changed places - and of course we aggravated and aggravated my mother so much that she come rushing in there
,
 and she knew the spot where I was laying - and she grabbed, not me, grabbed him you see by the head of the hair and got it and bashed it on the bed. 'Til he shouted blue murder it was him. And she dropped him like a brick and run out. And of course she c
o
uld - after she - cooled over her temper she could see the funny side of it, but - because you see, my mother was so worried, we - if she didn't get a letter within so many days from France she would start - walking about you know, wringing her hands and 
- no letter, no letter. I suppose she couldn't stand a lot of the noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Her nerves got bad did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes, they did get bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9379685\charrsid2953716 Did she suffer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716  from sleeplessness and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes. And - she would never go out, never go out anywhere. No enjoyment, no, not while my father was away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did she write quite frequently then herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Oh - she did. He did at times but - of course you know what it would be in the war, they would get delayed. Yes, he used to - I don't know if t
hey've still got them - my sister, I - she - she had 'em up 'til - when she was alive - often get a letter with a - rose in it, squashed, what he'd picked off the front of the trench. And see in the letter. Which when you come to think of it - was a - lov
ely gesture wasn't I.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It's strange to think of roses being in a place like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 These were wild roses were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, these were little - no - yes, cultivated roses. No, these wasn't - wasn't - you're talking of Flanders Poppy. N
o, this was - these were roses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Did your mother or father belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 No, only the - that - the loan - that was - used - they used to run these loans in pub. They belonged to that. For Christmastime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 That was the only one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 
Well that - wasn't only for Christmastime you see - these loans - what were run, you could - have a - what they called a sub. You could draw out four pound - between - the time you're paying it in and before Christmas and you used to have to pay it b
ack at so much extra. That's - why these loans - were run by different individuals to make a profit. And if you didn't have a loan - you were fined - so much, don't know if Mrs Kent knows all this but - you got fined. So you still didn't - you see - these
 people used to run these and make a huge profit out of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 You got out less than you put in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Yes, always. Whether you borrowed or whether you didn't. Shares they call them. They used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 If you got back less than you put in how did these clubs survive, I thought people would have lost confidence in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Well they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 It's like pawnshops, people lost money on them but they had to do it didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2099306 FK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14497874 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6825497\charrsid2953716 Do you remember people going to the pawnshops?
